Congratulatory Message to Syrian President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il sent a congratulatory message to Syrian President Bashar Al-Assad, who is regional secretary of the Arab Baath Socialist Party, on Wednesday on the occasion of his 43rd birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I extend the warmest congratulations to you on your 43rd birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Availing myself of this opportunity, I sincerely wish you happiness in good health and greater successes in your noble work to defend security of the country, achieve its development and prosperity and ensure lasting peace in the Middle East.

Performance "Arirang" Given to Celebrate 60th Birthday of DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- The Grand Gymnastic and Artistic Performance "Arirang", a Kim Il Sung Prize winner, was given at the May Day Stadium today in celebration of the 60th anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was enjoyed by senior party, army and state officials, chairpersons of friendly parties, deputies to the Supreme People's Assembly, officials of party, armed forces and power bodies, working people's organizations, public organizations, ministries and national institutions, anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters, officers and men of the Korean People's Army, officials in the fields of science, education, culture and arts, public health and the press, bereaved families of revolutionary martyrs, persons of merit and working people in Pyongyang.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on invitation to appreciate it were the chief of the Pyongyang mission of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front, congratulatory groups and delegations of overseas Koreans, including the congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan, and overseas compatriots who are staying in the socialist homeland to celebrate the 60th anniversary of the DPRK, representatives and staff members of foreign embassies and representatives of international organizations here, delegations of different countries, delegations of Juche idea study organizations and friendship and solidarity organizations and other foreign guests.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "Arirang" is a monumental masterpiece impressively depicting the history of sacred struggle of the Korean people who hewed out their destiny independently after having the great leader for the first time in the nation's history spanning 5,000 years and the army and people of the DPRK who are dynamically advancing toward the eminence of a great prosperous powerful nation with their enormous mental power and inexhaustible creative ingenuity, rallied as one in mind around the headquarters of the revolution.
 The performance began amid the playing of lilting melodies of song "Pyongyang Is Best".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers made an impressive grand epic representation of the undying feats of President Kim Il Sung who built a genuine people's country in Korea and leader Kim Jong Il who has raised the dignity and power of Kim Il Sung's Korea to the highest level with his unique Songun policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance was acclaimed by the audiences.

Kim Yong Nam Meets Foreigners 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, met and had a friendly talk with Giancarlo Elia Valori, chairman of the Development Bank of the Mediterranean and chairman of the Italian General Investment Group who is staying in the DPRK to celebrate the 60th birthday of the DPRK, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pak Kyong Son, vice department director of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, was on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim also met and had a talk with a delegation of the Kyodo News led by its President Satoshi Ishikawa on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Hong Son Ok, vice-chairperson of the Korean Society for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, and Kim Chang Gwang, vice-director general of the Korean Central News Agency.

Yang Hyong Sop Meets Cubans 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, met and had a talk at the Mansudae Assembly Hall today with Enrique Roman Hernandes, first vice-chairman of the Cuban Institute of Friendship with the Peoples, and his party staying in the DPRK to celebrate the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on the occasion were Paek Yong Ho, vice-chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, and Jose Manuel Galego Montano, Cuban ambassador to the DPRK.

Director General of UNESCO Here 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- Koitsiro Matsuura, director-general of the United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO), and his party arrived here today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were greeted at the airport by Pak Kil Yon, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, and Uma Thapa, acting UN resident coordinator to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 The government of the DPRK gave a reception in honor of the quests this evening

Art Performance Given to Mark 60th Birthday of DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- A music and dance performance "Song Dedicated to the Homeland of Songun" was given at the East Pyongyang Grand Theatre on Wednesday to celebrate the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was enjoyed by senior party, army and state officials, chairperson of a friendly party, officials of party, armed forces and power organs, public organizations, ministries and national institutions, officers and men of the Korean People's Army, officials in the fields of science, education, culture and arts, public health and the press and working people in the city of Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the audiences were overseas compatriots including the congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan staying in the socialist homeland to celebrate the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on invitation to enjoy the performance were diplomatic envoys of foreign embassies and members of the military attaches corps and representatives of international organizations here and foreign guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance began with chorus "Song of General Kim Il Sung", an immortal revolutionary paean. The repertoire included male solo "Song of River Amnok", dance "Azalea of the Motherland", female chorus "Song of New Spring", female instrumental ensemble "Pass of Mungyong", mixed quintet "Oh, My Motherland of Songun", violin solo and chorus "General, Here is the Forefront" and female vocal solo and chorus "Let's Love Our Country".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers loudly sang of the Korean people's deep reverence and trust in President Kim Il Sung, who built the socialist power centered on the popular masses in Korea to provide them with the eternal cradle of life, and General Secretary Kim Jong Il, who is guiding the revolutionary cause of Juche and the building of a great prosperous powerful nation always to victory with his unique Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance was acclaimed by the audiences.

Performance Given by Art Group Members of Schoolchildren's Palace 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- A performance was given by art group members of the Mangyongdae Schoolchildren's Palace on Wednesday to celebrate the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance began with prelude "We Also Came to Square of September". The repertoire included accordion ensemble "Care of Motherland", an immortal masterpiece, poem and song "My Country Represents the Whole Life of the Generalissimo" and male solo "General Represents Our Country".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers highly sang of the undying feats of President Kim Il Sung, who founded the DPRK and established the socialist system centered on the popular masses and General Secretary Kim Jong Il, who is bringing about the happiness of the rising generations and the prosperity of the country with his unique Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In chorus "Our Future Is Bright under the Care of the General", dancing tale "Five Marks That Pleased the General", folk chorus "My Country Is Best" and other numbers the performers successfully represented the bright and joyful looks of the younger generations who are stoutly growing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the audiences was Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea.

Great King of Cambodia Celebrates DPRK Birthday 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- Norodom Sihanouk, great king of Cambodia, sent a large basket of flowers to the DPRK embassy in Phnom Penh in celebration of the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Upon authorization of the great king, the delegation of the Ministry of the Royal Palace of the Cambodian government led by Kong Sam Ol, deputy prime minister in charge of the Royal Palace, visited the DPRK embassy on September 5 and laid the floral basket before the portraits of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il there.

Cambodian King Celebrates DPRK Birthday
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- Norodom Sihamoni, king of Cambodia, sent a large basket of flowers to the DPRK embassy in Phnom Penh in celebration of the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Upon authorization of the king, the delegation of the Ministry of the Royal Palace of the Cambodian government led by Kong Sam Ol, deputy prime minister in charge of the Royal Palace, visited the DPRK embassy on September 5 and laid the floral basket before the portraits of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il there.

Reception Given at DPRK Embassy in Beijing
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- A reception was given at the DPRK embassy in Beijing on September 8 to celebrate the 60th anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Jia Qinglin, member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the C.C., the Communist Party of China and chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, the deputy secretary general of the National Committee of the CPPCC, Chen Haosu, president of the Chinese People's Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries, Liu Hongcai, deputy head of the International Liaison Department of the CPC Central Committee, Wu Dawei, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, Chen Jian, vice-minister of Commerce, the vice-minister of Railways and officials concerned of the People's Daily Office, the Xinhua News Agency, the National Defence University, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 DPRK Ambassador to China Choe Jin Su and staff members of the embassy were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jia Qinglin said that today the Korean people are striving to fling open the door of a great prosperous powerful nation under the leadership of the Workers' Party of Korea headed by General Secretary Kim Jong Il. He sincerely wished the Korean people steady new successes in promoting the comprehensive development of economy and society and expanding external exchange and cooperation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the steadfast strategic policy of the Chinese party and government to constantly consolidate and develop the China-DPRK friendly and cooperative relations, he said, adding that China would make fresh contribution to ceaselessly promoting the development of the China-DPRK relations in the spirit of "inheriting tradition, facing the future and continuing good neighborliness and enhancing cooperation." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Choe Jin Su said that the army and people of the DPRK are now waging a dynamic struggle to firmly defend the Korean-style socialist system and build a great prosperous powerful nation true to the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will certainly attain the grand goal of building a rich and powerful country as long as there are the great Songun politics and the indomitable mental power of the army and people united as one in mind, he stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the consistent stand of the WPK and the DPRK government to value the DPRK-China friendship and steadily consolidate and develop it, he said, adding that the DPRK will strive to further expand and develop the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries in all fields.

Actions against American Beef Imports Staged in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- Actions against the import of American beef were waged in Seoul on September 6, according to CBS of south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The People's Measure Council against the Total Opening of south Korean Market to American Beef held a candlelight rally in Maroni Park in university street. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants in the rally charged that the Lee Myung Bak group is intensifying the suppression of the participants in the candlelight actions instead of meeting the demand of the people opposed to the American beef imports. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They declared that the people from all walks of life would stage a more vigorous struggle against the American beef imports, steadily holding the candlelight. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Christian organizations including the Korean Catholic Association for Justice held the 12th mass on situation in protest against the import of American beef and staged a street march to Seoul Railway Station. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The All-People Headquarters for Checking the Mad Cow Disease and other organizations conducted information activities accusing traitor Lee Myung Bak in Myongdong area.

Struggle against Lee Myung Bak Regime Urged in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- The Youth and Students Solidarity for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration in south Korea released an appeal titled "Let us all turn out in the struggle for resignation of the Lee Myung Bak regime" on Sept. 6. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The appeal charged that the Lee Myung Bak regime is enforcing treacherous and unpopular policies while oppressing the just demand of the people with violence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sycophantic and traitorous clan headed by Lee Myung Bak sold out the national interests to the outside forces while aggravating confrontation and tension between the south and the north and getting hell-bent on the suppression of the progressive forces, it pointed out, and said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If this grave situation goes on, the south Korean society will go back to the past period of dictatorship, the era of darkness. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The immediate goal of struggle is to drive the sycophantic and traitorous, undemocratic and unpopular Lee Myung Bak "government" into destruction. We should not stop the struggle against the present "government" but ceaselessly isolate and oppress it to accelerate its destruction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should hold the slogan "Defend the June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration!" in face of the Lee Myung Bak "government's" anti-reunification moves and pool the broad forces supporting the declarations and deal an intensive blow at the unpopular policies of the "government".

Kim Il Sung's Work Published in Italy
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il Sung's famous work "Let Us Shatter Imperialist Moves towards Aggression and War and Safeguard Peace and Independence" was brought out in booklet by the Struggle for the Peace and Socialism of Italy on September 3. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work, published on July 3, Juche 72 (1983), clarifies the idea that the most urgent and grave task facing the world progressive people is to struggle for peace and independence against the U.S. and other imperialists' moves for aggression and war.

DPRK Birthday Marked in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- Meetings were held in Hungary, Switzerland and Bangladesh on August 30 and September 1 to celebrate the 60th birthday of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed in the venues of the meetings were photos showing the immortal exploits of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Gyula Thurmer, chairman of the Hungarian Communist Workers' Party, noted that over the last 60 years after its foundation the DPRK has achieved signal successes in socialist construction and dynamically advanced along the road chosen by it while steadfastly keeping the revolutionary principle. And he hoped that the Workers' Party of Korea and the Korean people would make greater success in building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation under the leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Hungarian Communist Workers' Party will extend the constant support to the just cause of the WPK and the Korean people and strive to develop the friendly relations between the two countries, he said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Martin Lotscher, chairman of the Switzerland-Korea Committee, said that on September 9, 1948, Kim Il Sung founded the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, a sovereign and independent state in which the popular masses became masters of everything for the first time in the Korean history spanning 5,000 years, and enforced such popular policies as free medical care and free educational systems. He also beat the U.S. imperialists in the Fatherland Liberation War and reliably defended the freedom and sovereignty of the country by wisely leading the Korean army and people, the chairman stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Messages of greetings to Kim Jong Il were adopted at the meetings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, Korean book, photo, fine art work and handicraft exhibitions were opened in Mexico and Germany on August 28 and September 1 on the same occasion.

DPRK Birthday Observed in Equatorial Guinea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- The vice-director of the Department of International Relations of the Democratic Party of Equatorial Guinea who is representative of the party, paid a congratulatory visit to the DPRK embassy in his country on September 6 on the occasion of the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He made bows before the portraits of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Democratic Party and the people of Equatorial Guinea warmly congratulate the Workers' Party of Korea and the Democratic People's Republic of Korea on their achievements made under the wise leadership of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il, he said, hoping that the friendly and cooperative relations between the parties and peoples of the two countries would grow stronger in the future, too.

Birthday of DPRK Celebrated in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- Floral baskets were sent to DPRK embassies on September 3 and 5 in celebration of the 60th anniversary of the DPRK by the People's Party, the FUNCINPEC Party, the Khmer Democratic Party, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation, the Ministry of Commerce and the Ministry of Culture and Fine Arts of Cambodia, the Central Committee of the Communist Party (Marxist), the All India Agricultural Workers' Union, the Taekwon-Do Association and Juche idea study organizations in India and the Workers' Party, the People's Socialist Party, the Socialist Popular Party, the Committee for the Study of Kimilsungism, the Fellowship Institute to Honor the Memory of President Kim Il Sung, the Institute for the Study of the Juche Idea and the Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification in Mexico and the Mexico-Korea Friendship Association. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The floral baskets were laid before portraits of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il at the embassies.

Kim Jong Il envia mensaje de felicitacion al presidente siriaco
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 10 de septiembre (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea y Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, envio el dia 10 un mensaje de felicitacion al secretario de la Direccion Regional del Partido Socialista del Resurgimiento Arabe y presidente de la Republica Arabe de Siria Bashar al-Assad, con motivo del 43o aniversario de su natalicio. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
El mensaje senala en particular: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Le envio mi calurosa felicitacion a usted con motivo del aniversario 43 de su natalicio. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Aprovecho esta ocasion para desearle de todo corazon buena salud y felicidad y mayores exitos en su noble labor para defender la seguridad del pais, lograr su desarrollo y su prosperidad y preservar la paz duradera en la region del Medio Oriente.

Yang Hyong Sop se reune con Enrique Roman Hernandez
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 10 de septiembre (ATCC) -- El vicepresidente del Presidium de la Asamblea Popular Suprema de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, Yang Hyong Sop, charlo el dia 10 en el Palacio de los Congresos Mansudae con Enrique Roman Hernandez, primer vicepresidente del Instituto Cubano de Amistad con los Pueblos (ICAP), y su comitiva que permanecen actualmente en Corea con motivo del 60o aniversario de la fundacion de la RPDC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 En la ocasion estuvieron presentes el vicepresidente del Comite Coreano de Relaciones Culturales con el Extranjero Paek Yong Ho y el embajador extraordinario y plenipotenciario cubano en Corea Jose Manuel Galego Montano.
